docs.name: Cereal Production Index - Ireland
docs.description: Cereal Production Index for Ireland. Source: FAOSTAT. The FAO indices of cereal production show the relative level of the aggregate volume of cereal production for each year in comparison with the base period 1999-2001. They are based on the sum of price-weighted quantities of different cereals produced after deductions of quantities used as seed, weighted in a similar manner. The resulting aggregate represents, therefore, disposable production for any use except as seed. For more information, see http://faostat.fao.org/site/612/default.aspx#ancor.
